        h1 Landing Page Configuration
        p You may provide a landing page as part of the Service Portal, enabling users to navigate to the product of interest. If this is configured properly, users do no longer require direct access to a given BOM using the workspace ID and dms ID. Instead, they can click on a given product and with this open the matching service information of the related BOM.
        img(src='images/apps/services-portal-8.png' style='width:100%;max-height:722px;margin:10px 0px;')
        p In addition, they can track their formerly created spare parts requests.
        img(src='images/apps/services-portal-9.png' style='width:100%;max-height:915px;margin:10px 0px;')
        p With the default configuration, this capability involves the Products workspace. All products matching a defined search critieria will be displayed on the Landing Page. In addition, these products must link to the matching EBOM which will be used to open the given serivce information for the selected product.
        p Various configuration settings drive this landing page: productsFilter, productsSortBy, productsGroupBy, productsFieldImage, ... wsIdProducts. See their description in the next chapter.
        p The default configuration of the landing page uses the following settings: 
            ol 
                li All products of workspace 95 having an Engineering BOM will be shown (settings products.workspaceId and products.filter)
                li These products will be grouped by Product Line (setting products.groupBy)
                li Each product tile will show the image of field IMAGE as well as the products' TITLE and DESCRIPTION property values (settings products.fieldIdTileImage , products.fieldIdTileTitle and products.fieldIdTileSubtitle)
                li When users click a product, its field ENGINEERING_BOM will be used to open the related BOM and to open the matching Service Portal for this item (setting products.fieldIdBOM)
                li The header of the landing page's list of products is set to 'Serviceable Products' (settings products.headerLabel)
        p You can disable access to this landing page with the home button by setting 'features.homeButton = false'. See chapter 
            strong Feature Availability 
            |for details.
        h1 Configuration Settings
